# chronos

Detect timing errors in seismic data via ambient-noise cross-correlation.

Companion package [`chronfix/`](chronfix/) consumes the chronos
correction file and applies it to raw MiniSEED.

The HYS14 (OOI Hydrate Ridge OBS) clock fix is the worked example. See
[`docs/HYS14 — Correction Method.md`](docs/HYS14%20%E2%80%94%20Correction%20Method.md)
for the full write-up,
[`docs/HYS14 — Timing Diagnostic.md`](docs/HYS14%20%E2%80%94%20Timing%20Diagnostic.md)
for the diagnostic run,
[`docs/Chronos — Implementation Plan.md`](docs/Chronos%20%E2%80%94%20Implementation%20Plan.md)
for project background.

## Install

```bash
pip install -e .
```

## Pipeline

Each step is a CLI module under `chronos.scripts`. Outputs land under
`data/` (gitignored).

```bash
# 1. Pull MiniSEED + StationXML from FDSN
python -m chronos.scripts.download_data \
    --network OO --stations HYS12 HYS14 --channel MHZ \
    --workers 4

# 2. Daily inter-station ZZ cross-correlations (one or more pairs)
python -m chronos.scripts.compute_ccf --pairs HYS12-HYS14 --workers 8

# 3. Hourly ballistic peak-lag track (per pair)
python -m chronos.scripts.compute_peak_lag --pair HYS12-HYS14

# 4. Sign-flip + anchor + master-axis combine into Δt(target station)
python -m chronos.scripts.combine_clock \
    --target HYS14 --primary-pair HYS12-HYS14

# 5. Outlier filter + |Δdt| trigger detection — produces the correction file
python -m chronos.scripts.filter_and_triggers \
    --target HYS14 --primary-pair HYS12-HYS14
```

The correction file is the directory written under
`data/clock_estimate/<target>/`:

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `delta_t_hourly_clean.npy` | Cleaned hourly Δt (NaN where masked) |
| `hour_times.npy` | datetime64[h] master axis |
| `trigger_periods.csv` | Merged trigger intervals |
| `filter_and_triggers.png` | Diagnostic plot |

Pass that directory to `chronfix.scripts.apply_correction`.

## Layout

```
chronos/
├── README.md
├── pyproject.toml
├── docs/                       methods + project notes
├── src/chronos/
│   ├── __init__.py
│   └── scripts/                CLI drivers
│       ├── download_data.py
│       ├── compute_ccf.py
│       ├── compute_peak_lag.py
│       ├── combine_clock.py
│       ├── filter_and_triggers.py
│       └── plot_ccf.py
├── data/                       runtime outputs (gitignored)
└── chronfix/                   companion package (separate repo layout)
```

## Validation

After applying the correction, re-run chronos on the corrected data to
verify the clock error is gone:

```bash
python -m chronos.scripts.compute_ccf --pairs HYS12-HYS14 --tag corrected --workers 8 \
    --input-root-override HYS14=/data/wsd02/maleen_data/OOI-Data-corrected
python -m chronos.scripts.compute_peak_lag --pair HYS12-HYS14_corrected
```

The hourly peak-lag track on the corrected pair should be flat at the
anchor lag across the full record. See
[`docs/HYS14 — Correction Method.md`](docs/HYS14%20%E2%80%94%20Correction%20Method.md)
for the closed-loop validation.
